==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cadaverous
<hw>Ca*dav"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cadaverosus</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the appearance or
color of a dead human body; pale; ghastly; <as>as, a <ex>cadaverous</ex>
look</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to, or having the qualities of, a
dead body.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The scent <xex>cadaverous</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Ca*dav"er*ous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Ca*dav"er*ous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cadbait</ent>⟦br⟧
